[Patient] How much water should I drink daily?
[Educator] Aim for 1.5 to 2 liters of fluids daily.
[Patient] Can I drink soda or juice instead?
[Educator] Limit soda and juice, focus on water, herbal tea, and low-sodium broth.
[Patient] How can I track my fluid intake?
[Educator] Use a measuring cup or mark a bottle to monitor your daily intake.
[Patient] What if I feel thirsty all the time?
[Educator] Sip water throughout the day and try sugar-free gum or mints. 
[Patient] Can I drink alcohol with my heart condition?
[Educator] Limit alcohol intake to 1 drink per day, avoid binge drinking.